What it is supposed to be

This is the server-to-server exchange endpoint.

Flow:
	1.	Arthur Core redirects browser to:

https://actual-app/stub-server/post-login?code=abc123


	2.	The actual app backend reads code=abc123
	3.	The actual app backend calls Arthur Core:

POST /auth/handoff/exchange


	4.	Arthur Core:
	•	checks if abc123 exists in Redis
	•	checks if expired / used
	•	finds the real session
	•	returns user info
	•	deletes the handoff code

So yes — if that endpoint is not present in Arthur Core, the receiving app will fail.

